                "invention-title": "MANUFACTURE OF SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE"
            },
            "abstract": {
                "p": "PURPOSE:To form a buried layer of large effect of preventing alpha ray damage at a time of hydrogen ion implantation by a method wherein high-energy hydrogen ions are implanted to a p type Si substrate after element formation, and is converted into n type by later heat treatment. CONSTITUTION:After a DRAM100 of 1-transistor and 1-capacitor type is formed on the p type Si substrate 1 by a normal method, hydrogen ions are implanted in a projection trajectory larger than the depth of this DRAM region. Thereafter, the region with the above-mentioned implanted hydrogen ions is converted into n type by heat treatment. Since this manner enables the buried layer 11 preventing alpha ray damage to be formed at a time of hydrogen ion implantation, the manufacturing process can be simplified."
            }
